    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>The key is to call <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.4.2/docs/api/java/text/DateFormat.html#isLenient%28%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\">DateFormat#isLenient(<code>false</code>)</a> so it won't roll values that are out of range during parsing:</p>\n\n<pre><code>DateFormat format = new SimpleDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd\");\nformat.parse(\"2010-02-31\"); //=&gt; Ok, rolls to \"Wed Mar 03 00:00:00 PST 2010\".\nformat.setLenient(false);\nformat.parse(\"2010-02-31\"); //=&gt; Throws ParseException \"Unparseable date\".\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Of course, you can use any actual date format you require.</p>\n"
