  "title" : "Checking if a date exists or not in Java",
  "body" : "<p>Is there any predefined class in Java such that, if I pass it a date it should return if it is a valid date or not? For example if I pass it 31st of February of some year, then it should return false, and if the date exists then it should return me true, for any date of any year.</p>\n\n<p>And I also want a method that would tell me what weekday this particular date is. I went through the Calender class but I didn't get how to do this.</p>\n"
